💡 Key Concepts (VERY IMPORTANT)
✅ Why HAProxy?
External entry point
Load balancing across nodes
✅ Why NodePort?
To expose Gateway to outside world
✅ Why Gateway?
Advanced routing (better than Ingress)
✅ Why HTTPRoute?
Defines traffic rules (path-based routing)
✅ Why ClusterIP?
Internal communication only (secure)
🚨 Common Mistakes (you avoided)
HAProxy → ClusterIP ❌
Direct NodePort access ❌ (not production)
Skipping HTTPRoute ❌
🎯 Interview One-Line Answer

👉
“User traffic hits HAProxy, which forwards to Kubernetes NodePort exposing the Gateway. The Gateway uses HTTPRoute to route requests to a ClusterIP service, which then forwards traffic to the application pods.”